comments.body:
@DanielRosenwasser They cannot be defined as regular enums, because they don't exist at runtime; in other words the following Javascript will fail:

    var x = Excel.Constants.xl3DBar;

But they are still useful as [documented constant values](https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/20703#issuecomment-361914358).

I understand this is a problem when `--isolatedModules`, but my understanding was that the final fix will be to [error on files consuming enums this way when `--isolatedModules` has been set.](https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/20703#issuecomment-361434795).

AFAICT the only other alternative is to remove them entirely from the definition files. Is that what I should do?

